1
00:00:11,978 --> 00:00:14,022
I'm sorry, I couldn't hear you.

2
00:00:14,606 --> 00:00:15,899
What did you say?

3
00:00:17,776 --> 00:00:18,818
I'm pregnant.

4
00:00:21,529 --> 00:00:22,947
-Excuse me?
-I'm…

5
00:00:24,115 --> 00:00:25,867
pregnant with Ji-hoon's baby.

6
00:00:32,290 --> 00:00:33,124
You're…

7
00:00:34,793 --> 00:00:37,295
pregnant with Ji-hoon's baby?

8
00:00:38,213 --> 00:00:39,297
Yes.

9
00:00:43,093 --> 00:00:46,346
The police found a gram of methamphetamine

10
00:00:46,429 --> 00:00:48,556
in the pocket of Assemblyman Nam's son

11
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:51,309
whose body was found 15 days ago.

12
00:00:51,893 --> 00:00:54,771
According to Sinyang Police Station,

13
00:00:54,854 --> 00:00:56,689
they found a small resealable bag

14
00:00:56,773 --> 00:00:59,484
containing one gram of methamphetamine

15
00:00:59,567 --> 00:01:01,194
as well as a burner phone.

16
00:01:01,277 --> 00:01:03,279
To investigate the details of his death…

17
00:01:21,047 --> 00:01:22,006
Oh, right.

18
00:01:28,304 --> 00:01:29,347
Here.

19
00:01:30,723 --> 00:01:33,017
No, you don't have to show me this.

20
00:01:35,770 --> 00:01:37,063
And I also have this.

21
00:01:42,277 --> 00:01:44,446
The pregnancy test kit can be inaccurate,

22
00:01:44,529 --> 00:01:46,781
so I had a blood test
at the hospital yesterday.

23
00:01:48,992 --> 00:01:51,703
This number means I'm five weeks pregnant,

24
00:01:51,786 --> 00:01:53,621
so I got pregnant three weeks ago.

25
00:01:54,414 --> 00:01:56,958
That's about ten days after
Ji-hoon's release,

26
00:01:58,543 --> 00:02:00,336
and three or four days
before his accident.

27
00:02:02,255 --> 00:02:05,049
I can't really pinpoint the exact date.

28
00:02:06,634 --> 00:02:08,928
I said I'll take the sonogram next time.

29
00:02:15,059 --> 00:02:16,895
And this is just my normal belly.

30
00:02:28,281 --> 00:02:32,577
I should probably show you
a photo we took together,

31
00:02:33,119 --> 00:02:35,747
but I lost my phone yesterday…

32
00:02:40,001 --> 00:02:41,419
so I'll just tell you in words.

33
00:02:41,502 --> 00:02:44,672
Ji-hoon and I really dated.

34
00:02:46,883 --> 00:02:49,177
We met through mutual friends.

35
00:02:49,260 --> 00:02:52,013
You recently got him
a studio apartment, right?

36
00:02:52,096 --> 00:02:54,307
Unit 507, Ujeong Apartment. Split-level.

37
00:02:54,974 --> 00:02:56,476
We stayed there together.

38
00:03:11,407 --> 00:03:13,243
Did Ji-hoon know

39
00:03:13,868 --> 00:03:15,787
that you were pregnant, Soo-bin?

40
00:03:17,664 --> 00:03:18,665
No.

41
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:21,668
I only found out yesterday.

42
00:03:28,883 --> 00:03:30,301
Were you at the funeral hall?

43
00:03:31,594 --> 00:03:33,888
Yes, of course.

44
00:03:33,972 --> 00:03:36,391
Sinyang Funeral Home. That huge hall.

45
00:03:38,351 --> 00:03:40,770
I was a bit out of it on that day,

46
00:03:40,853 --> 00:03:44,774
but I don't recall
seeing any of Ji-hoon's friends.

47
00:03:45,817 --> 00:03:47,360
Nobody else came?

48
00:03:47,986 --> 00:03:49,404
I can't believe them.

49
00:03:50,238 --> 00:03:54,117
Don't worry about them.
They were probably all too shocked.

50
00:03:55,285 --> 00:03:58,746
I went alone,
but I didn't sign the guest book.

51
00:03:59,330 --> 00:04:00,540
It didn't feel right.

52
00:04:03,001 --> 00:04:04,794
There were a lot of visitors.

53
00:04:05,378 --> 00:04:07,880
I stood in line with strangers
and lit incense.

54
00:04:10,174 --> 00:04:11,634
It's fine if you can't remember.

55
00:04:15,930 --> 00:04:19,726
But I haven't been to his columbarium.

56
00:04:20,810 --> 00:04:22,103
I don't know where it is.

57
00:04:23,479 --> 00:04:26,107
Please take me with you next time.

58
00:04:29,777 --> 00:04:32,405
I want to say goodbye to him.

59
00:04:35,783 --> 00:04:38,578
Sure. Thank you.

60
00:04:45,335 --> 00:04:46,169
So…

61
00:04:47,003 --> 00:04:49,964
do your parents know about this situation?

62
00:04:51,674 --> 00:04:52,508
No.

63
00:04:53,384 --> 00:04:54,677
I don't have any parents.

64
00:04:55,178 --> 00:04:56,304
Just like you.

65
00:05:01,017 --> 00:05:02,769
Ji-hoon told me.

66
00:05:02,852 --> 00:05:04,645
I didn't do any digging.

67
00:05:08,608 --> 00:05:10,109
Speaking of which…

68
00:05:12,737 --> 00:05:15,031
could you let me stay here?

69
00:05:22,163 --> 00:05:24,165
THE ACCIDENT

70
00:05:27,877 --> 00:05:29,379
Come on, please.

71
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,965
Can you call me? It's urgent.

72
00:05:39,764 --> 00:05:42,183
ASSEMBLYMEN'S OFFICE

73
00:05:52,568 --> 00:05:54,237
YEO-JIN

74
00:06:06,958 --> 00:06:10,586
Would you like something to drink?

75
00:06:10,670 --> 00:06:12,547
I have coffee…

76
00:06:13,131 --> 00:06:14,882
Am I allowed to have coffee?

77
00:06:16,676 --> 00:06:19,762
I'm not sure.
Some people have one cup a day.

78
00:06:21,639 --> 00:06:23,891
Then I'll take juice or tea.

79
00:06:24,559 --> 00:06:25,768
Just to be safe.

80
00:06:27,395 --> 00:06:28,312
Sure.

81
00:07:01,429 --> 00:07:02,513
GREAT ASSEMBLYMAN AWARD

82
00:07:02,597 --> 00:07:03,765
Assemblyman Kang.

83
00:07:03,848 --> 00:07:06,017
ASSEMBLYMAN KANG SOON-HONG

84
00:07:09,562 --> 00:07:14,233
Goodness, look how incompetent he is.

85
00:07:14,317 --> 00:07:17,779
He let his son's narcotics case
get exposed in the news?

86
00:07:19,322 --> 00:07:22,200
"One must keep his home in peace
to reign the world in peace."

87
00:07:23,075 --> 00:07:27,079
How can he manage state affairs

88
00:07:27,163 --> 00:07:30,041
when he can't even bring up
his son properly?

89
00:07:32,543 --> 00:07:34,128
-Hyeong-tae.
-Yes, sir.

90
00:07:35,546 --> 00:07:37,507
Put on the National Assembly TV.

91
00:07:41,093 --> 00:07:42,929
Assemblyman Nam Joong-do
of the Daehan Party

92
00:07:43,012 --> 00:07:46,182
must take responsibility for covering up
his eldest son's drug possession,

93
00:07:46,265 --> 00:07:47,850
the suspicion of abuse

94
00:07:47,934 --> 00:07:50,937
for the special favor he called in
for an investigation

95
00:07:51,437 --> 00:07:53,981
at Sinyang Police Station,
and step down from his office.

96
00:07:54,482 --> 00:07:56,442
A simple runaway case
involving his daughter

97
00:07:56,526 --> 00:07:58,778
led to an emergency dispatch

98
00:07:58,861 --> 00:08:00,863
of 30 violent crime unit detectives.

99
00:08:00,947 --> 00:08:04,116
This is obviously an abuse of position
and power in his electoral district

100
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,661
by Assemblyman Nam Joong-do.

101
00:08:07,662 --> 00:08:09,831
To our people, Assemblyman Nam Joong-do…

102
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:15,336
There's a lot of malicious comments
calling him a junkie.

103
00:08:15,419 --> 00:08:16,629
We have no excuses.

104
00:08:16,712 --> 00:08:17,839
I mean, methamphetamine?

105
00:08:18,506 --> 00:08:22,009
I know I shouldn't speak ill of the dead,

106
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:25,221
but this is awful.
How are we going to patch this up?

107
00:08:25,930 --> 00:08:28,474
Honestly, if it didn't end here,

108
00:08:28,558 --> 00:08:30,017
he might have done something worse.

109
00:08:31,185 --> 00:08:33,729
The Nation and People's Party
is probably thrilled right now.

110
00:08:34,897 --> 00:08:37,817
They're conflating this
and his missing daughter's investigation.

111
00:08:38,901 --> 00:08:40,236
Who would sit around and wait

112
00:08:40,319 --> 00:08:42,864
when you can't reach
your teenage daughter all night?

113
00:08:42,947 --> 00:08:44,407
We pay taxes and have police stations

114
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:47,159
so that they can help us
when our kids go missing.

115
00:08:47,243 --> 00:08:48,536
And how could they do this…

116
00:08:50,538 --> 00:08:52,248
to someone who just lost his son?

117
00:08:52,832 --> 00:08:54,000
They're just awful.

118
00:08:55,877 --> 00:08:58,337
We're in Yeouido.
You know how it is in politics.

119
00:09:05,428 --> 00:09:09,724
ASSEMBLYMAN NAM JOONG-DO

120
00:09:19,358 --> 00:09:22,945
NEW MESSAGES
MISSED CALLS

121
00:09:32,914 --> 00:09:34,498
Hello, Chief.

122
00:09:44,842 --> 00:09:47,803
Is there something you want to say to me?

123
00:09:51,057 --> 00:09:52,391
Well, by any chance…

124
00:09:52,975 --> 00:09:54,268
Yes?

125
00:09:56,187 --> 00:09:57,730
Did Ji-hoon…

126
00:10:13,746 --> 00:10:14,747
Hello.

127
00:10:15,665 --> 00:10:17,917
Nice to meet you.

128
00:10:24,465 --> 00:10:25,883
You lost your phone,

129
00:10:25,967 --> 00:10:28,552
so you don't have any photos of him
or text messages?

130
00:10:29,387 --> 00:10:31,764
Then how are we supposed to believe

131
00:10:31,847 --> 00:10:34,392
that you and Ji-hoon were
in a relationship?

132
00:10:36,602 --> 00:10:38,854
I already explained everything to her.

133
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:41,857
Do you want me to make a drawing
of his apartment unit?

134
00:10:41,941 --> 00:10:44,860
That's information
that all his other friends could have.

135
00:10:44,944 --> 00:10:46,362
I lived there with him.

136
00:10:48,656 --> 00:10:51,909
Ji-hoon got into this incident
fifteen days after his release.

137
00:10:52,785 --> 00:10:55,371
I think it's an exaggeration

138
00:10:55,454 --> 00:10:59,291
to say you lived with him
after spending 15 days together.

139
00:11:00,876 --> 00:11:03,212
Fifteen days aren't that short.

140
00:11:04,213 --> 00:11:06,090
We did everything we possibly could.

141
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:12,221
You may not have met your parents
after their divorce,

142
00:11:12,304 --> 00:11:13,347
but you have their numbers, right?

143
00:11:13,431 --> 00:11:14,557
No.

144
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,308
I don't even know where they live.

145
00:11:16,392 --> 00:11:18,436
Do you have any other guardians?

146
00:11:19,437 --> 00:11:20,563
There aren't any.

147
00:11:21,897 --> 00:11:24,900
I'm an adult. I'm not a teenager.

148
00:11:26,610 --> 00:11:27,862
I don't even know your age.

149
00:11:28,696 --> 00:11:30,364
How old are you? What about school?

150
00:11:30,448 --> 00:11:31,657
I was born in 2001.

151
00:11:33,117 --> 00:11:34,994
The same as Ji-hoon. I'm 22.

152
00:11:35,494 --> 00:11:36,871
I dropped out of Seongseol High.

153
00:11:37,705 --> 00:11:40,124
And I wasn't expelled.

154
00:11:40,708 --> 00:11:41,625
I just didn't want to go.

155
00:11:48,758 --> 00:11:50,092
Will you

156
00:11:51,177 --> 00:11:52,136
have the baby?

157
00:11:55,306 --> 00:11:57,850
I don't know. What should I do?

158
00:11:59,643 --> 00:12:00,603
My goodness.

159
00:12:01,437 --> 00:12:02,605
Hye-joo.

160
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:04,106
Did you hear that?

161
00:12:04,774 --> 00:12:05,816
You did, right?

162
00:12:06,484 --> 00:12:07,443
Unbelievable.

163
00:12:15,242 --> 00:12:18,913
His blood tested negative
for blood tests for illegal drugs,

164
00:12:18,996 --> 00:12:23,042
but his blood alcohol level was
at a level of acute alcohol intoxication.

165
00:12:23,876 --> 00:12:26,045
-I see.
-I tried not to let the news get out

166
00:12:26,128 --> 00:12:28,339
about your son's drug possession, but…

167
00:12:29,548 --> 00:12:31,008
I'm sorry.

168
00:12:31,091 --> 00:12:31,967
It's okay.

169
00:12:32,885 --> 00:12:35,221
I didn't expect it to be hidden forever.

170
00:12:37,306 --> 00:12:38,390
But Assemblyman Nam.

171
00:12:38,974 --> 00:12:41,477
Narcotics made a series
of arrests recently,

172
00:12:42,061 --> 00:12:45,314
and they discovered a connection
to your son's burner phone.

173
00:12:46,565 --> 00:12:48,943
And according to a confession,
one of the drop-off points

174
00:12:49,610 --> 00:12:51,946
includes a restroom
on the bank of the Han River.

175
00:12:53,197 --> 00:12:55,574
And your son was caught on the camera…

176
00:13:02,623 --> 00:13:04,959
at the entrance of the restroom.

177
00:13:37,825 --> 00:13:40,035
You haven't heard from Joong-do yet?

178
00:13:40,119 --> 00:13:43,539
No, I left him a message,
but he hasn't called. He must be busy.

179
00:13:44,373 --> 00:13:45,749
So I haven't called again.

180
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:48,502
Right. He'll be home later anyway.

181
00:13:56,468 --> 00:13:57,928
Yeo-jin, excuse me.

182
00:14:00,514 --> 00:14:01,765
Hey, Yoon-seo.

183
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:05,811
Right, okay.

184
00:14:13,527 --> 00:14:17,114
Who's Yoon-seo?

185
00:14:18,282 --> 00:14:21,410
I'm guessing Ji-hoon never told you
about his younger sister.

186
00:14:23,245 --> 00:14:25,164
I see.

187
00:14:32,755 --> 00:14:34,965
I don't know why
they found it in his pocket,

188
00:14:35,049 --> 00:14:37,384
but I'm sure that it wasn't his.

189
00:14:37,468 --> 00:14:39,261
Everything is okay with Dad too,

190
00:14:39,345 --> 00:14:42,139
so focus on your class,
and come straight home afterward.

191
00:14:42,223 --> 00:14:43,140
Okay?

192
00:14:44,141 --> 00:14:45,351
Come straight home.

193
00:14:50,773 --> 00:14:52,191
NEWS

194
00:14:54,652 --> 00:14:57,404
NAM PRESSED TO RESIGN
DUE TO SCANDAL SURROUNDING HIS CHILDREN

195
00:15:04,703 --> 00:15:06,997
I'm pleased that
we were able to build new roads

196
00:15:07,081 --> 00:15:08,499
for Seonghan District 2

197
00:15:08,582 --> 00:15:10,876
as part of the public redevelopment plan.

198
00:15:12,044 --> 00:15:14,755
The residents here
have suffered long enough

199
00:15:14,838 --> 00:15:18,425
because of the deteriorating
roads and buildings.

200
00:15:18,509 --> 00:15:19,718
-Yes.
-He's right.

201
00:15:19,802 --> 00:15:23,097
The project was delayed
because it lacked business potential.

202
00:15:24,473 --> 00:15:26,183
Let me pour you a glass.

203
00:15:26,684 --> 00:15:28,852
Assemblyman Nam, allow me to pour you one.

204
00:15:28,936 --> 00:15:31,105
-Goodness.
-There's no need for formalities.

205
00:15:31,188 --> 00:15:33,023
Goodness, thank you.

206
00:15:33,107 --> 00:15:36,694
Thank you for joining us for a meeting
despite the circumstances.

207
00:15:36,777 --> 00:15:38,862
Of course, I should be here. Thank you.

208
00:15:38,946 --> 00:15:40,572
Cheer up, Assemblyman Nam.

209
00:15:40,656 --> 00:15:42,449
Thank you.

210
00:15:42,533 --> 00:15:43,534
Sure thing.

211
00:15:43,617 --> 00:15:44,743
He can really drink.

212
00:15:45,327 --> 00:15:46,787
-Let me pour you one.
-Thank you.

213
00:15:47,454 --> 00:15:49,373
RESERVATIONS
ROOM 1, JICHEONG HIGH, 41ST CLASS

214
00:15:49,456 --> 00:15:50,624
It must have been tough.

215
00:15:52,126 --> 00:15:53,294
You could use a drink.

216
00:15:54,295 --> 00:15:55,254
Thanks for coming.

217
00:15:55,337 --> 00:15:59,133
Work is important,
but come out and meet us too.

218
00:15:59,216 --> 00:16:01,010
-Sure.
-Cheers.

219
00:16:01,093 --> 00:16:03,637
-To Jicheong High!
-Jicheong High!

220
00:16:06,765 --> 00:16:09,435
You've got to meet people.

221
00:16:09,518 --> 00:16:11,061
STOP LYING. WE KNOW IT WAS METH.
R.I.P. MR. JUNKIE

222
00:16:11,145 --> 00:16:12,521
Everything will be fine.

223
00:16:12,604 --> 00:16:14,982
-To Jicheong High!
-Jicheong High!

224
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:18,152
We're meeting again next time.

225
00:16:18,235 --> 00:16:19,653
Of course.

226
00:16:19,737 --> 00:16:21,280
-Joong-do.
-See you later.

227
00:16:21,363 --> 00:16:23,449
Let's grab a drink soon.

228
00:16:23,532 --> 00:16:25,242
-Okay, I'll be in touch.
-Okay.

229
00:16:25,326 --> 00:16:27,286
-Please drive safely.
-Sure.

230
00:16:27,369 --> 00:16:28,495
Let's go.

231
