Please get the car ready.

232
00:16:39,089 --> 00:16:40,049
Are you all right, sir?

233
00:16:40,674 --> 00:16:41,717
I'm fine.

234
00:17:15,709 --> 00:17:16,794
Ms. Kim.

235
00:17:19,588 --> 00:17:20,589
She's coming.

236
00:17:24,927 --> 00:17:26,136
Hello.

237
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:27,763
-Hello.
-Hello.

238
00:17:28,555 --> 00:17:31,600
Assemblyman Nam had
a little too much to drink today.

239
00:17:32,351 --> 00:17:33,852
He rarely does that.

240
00:17:34,436 --> 00:17:36,063
-I'm sorry.
-It's okay.

241
00:17:36,146 --> 00:17:37,815
Let me escort him inside.

242
00:17:37,898 --> 00:17:38,816
Actually, Woo-jae…

243
00:17:51,495 --> 00:17:52,579
So?

244
00:17:53,747 --> 00:17:54,832
What does she want?

245
00:17:55,749 --> 00:17:58,585
She wants a place to stay.
She has nowhere to go.

246
00:18:02,673 --> 00:18:05,968
What about the baby? What's her plan?

247
00:18:08,011 --> 00:18:09,555
She doesn't know yet.

248
00:18:11,348 --> 00:18:12,349
She doesn't know?

249
00:18:14,143 --> 00:18:16,145
She must be a bit confused about it all.

250
00:18:17,062 --> 00:18:18,522
She's young

251
00:18:19,398 --> 00:18:21,150
and her pregnancy was out of the blue.

252
00:18:23,402 --> 00:18:24,278
And…

253
00:18:25,612 --> 00:18:27,156
Ji-hoon isn't around either.

254
00:18:32,828 --> 00:18:33,996
But honey.

255
00:18:36,165 --> 00:18:37,374
As for the baby,

256
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:40,711
whatever she decides to do with her baby,

257
00:18:40,794 --> 00:18:44,381
we don't have any right
to tell her what to do.

258
00:18:44,465 --> 00:18:45,424
You know that, right?

259
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:47,676
I know.

260
00:18:47,759 --> 00:18:48,927
I do…

261
00:18:50,012 --> 00:18:53,390
but even so, she barged in and asked you
to let her stay without any plans?

262
00:18:54,016 --> 00:18:56,643
I told you. She has no money
and nowhere to go.

263
00:18:56,727 --> 00:18:58,979
If we let her stay for a few days,

264
00:18:59,062 --> 00:19:01,482
she'll figure out what to do.

265
00:19:05,402 --> 00:19:07,196
I'll tell her she can stay for--

266
00:19:07,279 --> 00:19:08,489
No, send her elsewhere.

267
00:19:09,698 --> 00:19:11,033
Can you look into it?

268
00:19:12,701 --> 00:19:13,827
Elsewhere? Why?

269
00:19:14,786 --> 00:19:15,787
I don't want her.

270
00:19:17,289 --> 00:19:19,333
-You don't want her?
-No, I don't.

271
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,502
I don't want her in our home.

272
00:19:22,544 --> 00:19:23,504
Wait.

273
00:19:25,923 --> 00:19:27,216
I mean, honey.

274
00:19:29,259 --> 00:19:31,720
She's pregnant with Ji-hoon's child

275
00:19:31,803 --> 00:19:33,347
and she had nowhere to go.

276
00:19:33,430 --> 00:19:36,808
And you want me to send her away
just because you don't want her?

277
00:19:38,519 --> 00:19:40,395
Why do you want to let her stay so badly?

278
00:19:45,526 --> 00:19:49,363
She just reminds me of myself.

279
00:19:51,823 --> 00:19:54,785
She has no parents, no money,
and nowhere to go.

280
00:19:54,868 --> 00:19:56,453
YEONGSAN TO GANGNAM

281
00:19:56,537 --> 00:19:58,497
It reminds me of myself…

282
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:01,625
What took you so long?

283
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:04,378
-…when I first came to Seoul.
-Goodness.

284
00:20:09,675 --> 00:20:11,927
I know how it feels to be alone

285
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:14,763
with nobody to depend on.

286
00:20:14,846 --> 00:20:18,267
How can I tell her to go elsewhere
when I have a perfectly fine home?

287
00:20:24,022 --> 00:20:27,943
And I was just her age
when I had Yoon-seo.

288
00:20:28,026 --> 00:20:29,945
At least I had you then.

289
00:20:31,613 --> 00:20:33,365
But she's completely alone.

290
00:20:36,827 --> 00:20:37,744
Do you believe her?

291
00:20:38,996 --> 00:20:40,622
That Ji-hoon is the father?

292
00:20:42,499 --> 00:20:43,792
Honey.

293
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:46,712
How can you believe her? Can she prove it?

294
00:20:47,921 --> 00:20:48,922
No, right?

295
00:20:49,923 --> 00:20:51,216
So how can you believe her?

296
00:20:55,012 --> 00:20:56,013
What about you?

297
00:20:57,598 --> 00:21:00,392
How do you know Yoon-seo is your daughter?

298
00:21:17,492 --> 00:21:18,660
Hello.

299
00:21:19,369 --> 00:21:20,203
Nice to meet you.

300
00:21:22,664 --> 00:21:23,498
Honey.

301
00:21:36,094 --> 00:21:37,471
Is Ji-hoon really the father?

302
00:21:38,764 --> 00:21:39,765
Honey.

303
00:21:44,227 --> 00:21:46,563
Don't lie to me. Is it true?

304
00:21:48,940 --> 00:21:49,775
Yes.

305
00:21:51,568 --> 00:21:54,446
Honey, let's talk tomorrow.
You had too much to drink.

306
00:21:55,113 --> 00:21:57,407
Do you want to know
when, where, and how we did it?

307
00:21:58,033 --> 00:22:00,327
Or whether he was any good?

308
00:22:05,749 --> 00:22:07,250
I guess you don't want to believe it.

309
00:22:08,001 --> 00:22:09,044
Fine.

310
00:22:09,669 --> 00:22:10,504
I understand.

311
00:22:12,005 --> 00:22:14,341
I'll get an abortion.

312
00:22:15,884 --> 00:22:18,553
-Wait…
-I heard it's not illegal anymore.

313
00:22:20,597 --> 00:22:22,265
It'll look great on the news too.

314
00:22:23,016 --> 00:22:25,185
I had a kid with an assemblyman's son,

315
00:22:25,268 --> 00:22:27,187
but they kicked me out of their house.

316
00:22:29,064 --> 00:22:29,981
Interesting, right?

317
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:36,071
Hey.

318
00:22:37,697 --> 00:22:38,532
Yoon-seo.

319
00:22:38,615 --> 00:22:40,534
-Watch what you say.
-Yoon-seo.

320
00:22:40,617 --> 00:22:43,161
My dad isn't someone
you can talk to like that.

321
00:22:43,245 --> 00:22:46,123
And the same goes for Nam Ji-hoon.

322
00:22:46,206 --> 00:22:48,583
-No matter how big of a scumbag he was--
-Scumbag?

323
00:22:49,918 --> 00:22:51,002
Hey.

324
00:22:57,092 --> 00:22:59,136
I never thought he was a scumbag.

325
00:23:01,638 --> 00:23:03,140
That's why I'm in this mess.

326
00:23:04,474 --> 00:23:05,475
This mess?

327
00:23:06,059 --> 00:23:09,354
Yes, you got into this mess
because you live like that.

328
00:23:09,438 --> 00:23:11,064
-That's enough, Yoon-seo.
-You're right.

329
00:23:13,150 --> 00:23:15,026
And that's why Nam Ji-hoon
ended up like that.

330
00:23:15,777 --> 00:23:17,028
-Soo-bin.
-What?

331
00:23:17,112 --> 00:23:19,114
Hey, are you done?

332
00:23:19,197 --> 00:23:21,616
-Yoon-seo, what's with you?
-Let go of me, Mom!

333
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:23,743
-You crazy bitch.
-That's enough, Yoon-seo.

334
00:23:23,827 --> 00:23:26,329
Do you even hear yourself?
You got him into drugs, didn't you?

335
00:23:26,413 --> 00:23:28,123
-It was yours, isn't it?
-Drugs?

336
00:23:28,206 --> 00:23:29,708
-Yoon-seo.
-Yes, drugs!

337
00:23:29,791 --> 00:23:32,335
They found meth on Ji-hoon.
Wasn't it yours?

338
00:23:32,419 --> 00:23:33,503
It wasn't me.

339
00:23:33,587 --> 00:23:34,504
It really wasn't me.

340
00:23:35,338 --> 00:23:36,840
I don't know anything about that.

341
00:23:36,923 --> 00:23:38,800
-Stop pretending!
-Nam Yoon-seo!

342
00:23:40,135 --> 00:23:41,303
I told you to stop.

343
00:23:42,512 --> 00:23:43,722
You should also watch it.

344
00:23:45,098 --> 00:23:45,932
Dad.

345
00:23:46,016 --> 00:23:47,851
She's just a crazy bitch.

346
00:23:47,934 --> 00:23:49,603
So just kick her out now.

347
00:23:49,686 --> 00:23:51,688
Yoon-seo, cut it out and go upstairs.

348
00:23:51,771 --> 00:23:54,232
-Yeo-jin, can you take her?
-Yoon-seo, let's go up--

349
00:23:54,316 --> 00:23:57,819
-No, I'm not going up.
-That's enough! The adults are talking!

350
00:23:57,903 --> 00:23:58,737
Why?

351
00:23:58,820 --> 00:24:00,906
Why do I have to stay out of it?

352
00:24:00,989 --> 00:24:03,366
I'm a part of this family too.
I'm Ji-hoon's sister!

353
00:24:03,450 --> 00:24:05,577
-Nam Yoon-seo!
-To be frank,

354
00:24:06,161 --> 00:24:08,997
I used to wish
that he would die all the time.

355
00:24:09,748 --> 00:24:12,042
He always ended up on the news
and got in Dad's way

356
00:24:12,125 --> 00:24:13,293
and broke your heart.

357
00:24:14,211 --> 00:24:15,086
So I wished…

358
00:24:16,296 --> 00:24:19,257
that he would just die all the time.

359
00:24:20,425 --> 00:24:21,384
But…

360
00:24:22,594 --> 00:24:24,846
But I didn't think he actually would.

361
00:24:34,648 --> 00:24:36,691
You said that he was a scumbag yourself.

362
00:24:39,819 --> 00:24:42,822
Yes, and you're pregnant
with a scumbag's kid.

363
00:24:42,906 --> 00:24:44,449
-Congratulations.
-Nam Yoon-seo!

364
00:24:44,533 --> 00:24:46,159
That's enough, Nam Yoon-seo!

365
00:24:48,119 --> 00:24:49,246
Why?

366
00:24:49,329 --> 00:24:51,164
Why are you yelling at me?

367
00:25:07,639 --> 00:25:08,598
That's enough.

368
00:25:10,183 --> 00:25:12,143
It doesn't matter if what you say is true.

369
00:25:13,061 --> 00:25:14,938
This is Ji-hoon's home,
and they're his family.

370
00:25:16,439 --> 00:25:18,483
Are you here to blackmail them?

371
00:25:18,567 --> 00:25:20,277
You're not.

372
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:23,113
But if you keep running your mouth
like you are right now,

373
00:25:23,697 --> 00:25:25,073
that's what you'd be doing.

374
00:25:27,033 --> 00:25:28,076
But that's not you.

375
00:25:28,910 --> 00:25:31,371
You got pregnant while dating him,

376
00:25:31,454 --> 00:25:33,540
and Ji-hoon got into
an unfortunate accident.

377
00:25:34,416 --> 00:25:36,376
That's why you came to his parents' house.

378
00:25:37,794 --> 00:25:39,337
You didn't have any ulterior motives.

379
00:25:40,130 --> 00:25:40,964
Right?

380
00:26:02,611 --> 00:26:04,738
You can stay in Ji-hoon's room for now.

381
00:26:06,615 --> 00:26:08,575
This is the bathroom.

382
00:26:08,658 --> 00:26:09,701
And his room is…

383
00:26:16,333 --> 00:26:18,335
this way. Follow me.

384
00:26:32,182 --> 00:26:33,183
Yes?

385
00:26:39,105 --> 00:26:40,065
Here.

386
00:26:41,941 --> 00:26:44,944
I'm not sure if these clothes will fit.

387
00:26:48,990 --> 00:26:52,786
My room is right across from you,
so let me know if you need anything.

388
00:26:54,371 --> 00:26:55,205
Okay.

389
00:26:58,124 --> 00:26:59,250
Get some rest, then.

390
00:27:04,005 --> 00:27:07,258
Actually, there's something
I meant to ask you.

391
00:27:09,719 --> 00:27:10,553
Sure.

392
00:27:11,805 --> 00:27:13,139
By any chance, did Ji-hoon…

393
00:27:16,017 --> 00:27:20,271
force you in any way without your consent?

394
00:27:28,154 --> 00:27:29,197
Did he force himself on me?

395
00:27:32,575 --> 00:27:33,618
No, it wasn't like that.

396
00:27:36,037 --> 00:27:38,206
Ji-hoon wasn't that low.

397
00:27:38,707 --> 00:27:41,251
If he had, I would be at a police station.

398
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:46,715
Right.

399
00:27:48,383 --> 00:27:50,093
Okay, then. Get some rest.

400
00:28:43,146 --> 00:28:46,107
Please head inside.
I'm going to have a smoke.

401
00:28:47,901 --> 00:28:49,235
May I have one too?

402
00:28:58,661 --> 00:29:00,080
I didn't know you smoked.

403
00:29:01,873 --> 00:29:03,500
I quit on the day of the ruling.

404
00:29:04,125 --> 00:29:07,837
It felt so unfair
that I wanted to live long.

405
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:25,730
It's been a while since we saw
each other over Ji-hoon's case.

406
00:29:25,814 --> 00:29:28,233
It was so hectic
that I didn't even get to say hi.

407
00:29:29,025 --> 00:29:31,236
-Have you been well?
-Yes, I'm all right.

408
00:29:32,570 --> 00:29:34,864
-Have you been well?
-Yes.

409
00:29:37,784 --> 00:29:39,828
What should we do with her?

410
00:29:39,911 --> 00:29:42,163
She doesn't know
if she'll have the baby or not.

411
00:29:45,333 --> 00:29:47,210
If she wants an abortion,

412
00:29:47,293 --> 00:29:50,797
we just have to make sure
we didn't pressure her, and that's it.

413
00:29:51,381 --> 00:29:54,509
Don't look for a hospital
or pay for her fees.

414
00:29:54,592 --> 00:29:56,302
We can't have anything to do with it.

415
00:29:56,970 --> 00:29:58,221
Okay.

416
00:29:58,304 --> 00:29:59,973
But what if she wants to keep it?

417
00:30:00,056 --> 00:30:02,642
That's not bad news for Assemblyman Nam.

418
00:30:03,309 --> 00:30:06,563
It could be used
to appeal to the pro-life side.

419
00:30:08,148 --> 00:30:09,190
As you know,

420
00:30:10,358 --> 00:30:13,403
you never know which side's votes
you'll need in politics.

421
00:30:14,487 --> 00:30:16,364
If we need their votes, we'll use that.

422
00:30:17,198 --> 00:30:20,702
And if she gives birth,
leaves the baby here,

423
00:30:20,785 --> 00:30:22,579
and Ms. Kim ends up raising him,

424
00:30:24,247 --> 00:30:25,874
that will be an even better story.

425
00:30:25,957 --> 00:30:28,084
It will be a touching story.

426
00:30:32,255 --> 00:30:35,049
It seems like you're all ready
for the general election.

427
00:30:35,133 --> 00:30:36,426
The general election?

428
00:30:36,509 --> 00:30:37,343
I guess so.

429
00:30:37,427 --> 00:30:40,263
This general election,
and the one after this…

430
00:30:41,431 --> 00:30:42,432
I should be prepared.

431
00:30:46,311 --> 00:30:48,938
I'll take it. I'll throw it out at home.

432
00:30:49,022 --> 00:30:50,398
It's all right. Right here.

433
00:30:51,858 --> 00:30:53,276
I can put it in here.

434
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:55,904
You carry that around too?

435
00:31:03,786 --> 00:31:06,748
The moment any evidence is left behind,
I'll become a lawbreaker.

436
00:31:07,665 --> 00:31:09,626
I can't hold Assemblyman Nam back

437
00:31:09,709 --> 00:31:12,086
from doing great work in the future.

438
00:31:13,046 --> 00:31:15,590
I'm saying all kinds of nonsense today.

439
00:31:16,424 --> 00:31:17,634
I'll get going.

440
00:31:17,717 --> 00:31:19,469
-Goodbye, then.
-Get home safely.

441
00:31:26,476 --> 00:31:28,353
You should make that your last cigarette.

442
00:31:29,812 --> 00:31:31,397
You should live a long life.

443
00:31:31,481 --> 00:31:32,523
Goodbye.

444
00:32:00,635 --> 00:32:03,221
Too many things are
happening to us lately.

445
00:32:07,475 --> 00:32:09,143
I saw the news earlier.

446
00:32:09,894 --> 00:32:12,438
They say you received special favor
in the investigation.

447
00:32:13,940 --> 00:32:15,566
You don't need to worry about it.

448
00:32:16,943 --> 00:32:18,945
That will blow over soon.

449
00:32:20,071 --> 00:32:21,531
It's not a big deal.

450
00:32:28,538 --> 00:32:29,372
Right.

451
00:32:30,498 --> 00:32:33,042
Take that girl to a hospital
and get her tested for drugs.

452
00:32:33,918 --> 00:32:34,836
Drugs?

453
00:32:34,919 --> 00:32:38,047
Drug testing is mandatory for teachers,
and a lot of hospitals do it.

454
00:32:39,132 --> 00:32:41,718
Call and find a hospital
that reports same-day results.

455
00:32:42,343 --> 00:32:44,095
Do we really have to go that far?

456
00:32:45,179 --> 00:32:48,683
You saw how alarmed she was
when Yoon-seo mentioned drugs.

457
00:32:49,684 --> 00:32:50,601
It wasn't her.

458
00:32:54,731 --> 00:32:56,024
Think rationally.

459
00:32:56,983 --> 00:32:58,860
You'll want to believe she's a good girl,

460
00:32:58,943 --> 00:33:00,528
